## Public Member Functions

### releaseMemory() {#afba6ea5f221b263dbdde07f76ef96340}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="void WebAssemblyCFGStackify::releaseMemory ()"
  labels = {["virtual"]}>
<a href="#afba6ea5f221b263dbdde07f76ef96340">releaseMemory()</a> - This member can be implemented by a pass if it wants to be able to release its memory when it is no longer needed.

The default behavior of passes is to hold onto memory for the entire duration of their lifetime (which is the entire compile time). For pipelined passes, this is not a big deal because that memory gets recycled every time the pass is invoked on another program unit. For IP passes, it is more important to free memory when it is unused.

Optionally implement this function to release pass memory when it is no longer used.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/webassembly/webassemblycfgstackify-cpp/#l00175">175</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/webassembly/webassemblycfgstackify-cpp">WebAssemblyCFGStackify.cpp</a>.

### fixEndsAtEndOfFunction() {#af2ca817f27d32dcf814ebca487993650}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void WebAssemblyCFGStackify::fixEndsAtEndOfFunction (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/machinefunction">MachineFunction</a> &amp; MF)</>}>
In normal assembly languages, when the end of a function is unreachable, because the function ends in an infinite loop or a noreturn call or similar, it isn&#39;t necessary to worry about the function return type at the end of the function, because it&#39;s never reached.

However, in <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/webassembly">WebAssembly</a>, blocks that end at the function end need to have a return type signature that matches the function signature, even though it&#39;s unreachable. This function checks for such cases and fixes up the signatures.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/webassembly/webassemblycfgstackify-cpp/#l00105">105</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/webassembly/webassemblycfgstackify-cpp">WebAssemblyCFGStackify.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
